<p align="center">_____________________________</p>
<p align="center"><strong style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->HELP HIHOHIHO KEEP GOING OFF TO WORK</strong></p>
<p>Bill Law's Career-learning Caf&eacute; is in danger of closure. &nbsp;It has&nbsp;supported learning-for-living&nbsp;for approaching twenty years. &nbsp;It welcomes visitors, from careers-work and education outfits, working on enabling career management. &nbsp;It is independent of business, government and professional interests.&nbsp; Its material is free to access and download. &nbsp;Vistors are asked only to acknowledge caf&eacute; sources, and to feedback suggestions for their improvement.</p>
<p>But the caf&eacute; cannot go on indefinitely.&nbsp; It has been funded from Bill's earnings from his research-and-development work.&nbsp; That money will run out - the caf&eacute; needs new funding.&nbsp; Part of that comes from a scheme offering on-line professional mentoring in enabling career-management. &nbsp;There is an award of a Career-learning Caf&eacute; <a href="http://www.hihohiho.com/storyboarding/sblicence.pdf">certificate or diploma</a>.</p>
<p>Further arrangements must take account of the caf&eacute;'s users.&nbsp; They include people...</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->...not in a position to contribute - for them things will go on as they are for as long as possible</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->...in a position to contribute - who can decide for themselves what would be an affordable contribution</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->...in an organisation - who might be able to ask their managers to consider contributing</p>
<p>Contributors will prolong the caf&eacute;'s life - for themselves and for people in no position to help. &nbsp;If you or your outfit is in a position to help contact <a href="mailto:bill@hihohiho.com">Bill </a>about setting up your preferred procedure.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
